OL,7,FDefending Henry, Sol Hartley said he
OL,8,Fwas genuinely remorseful and wanted to
OL,9,Fchange his ways, adding the offending
OL,10,Fwas caused, in part, by his insecurity.
OL,12,FHowever, the judge said he agreed with
OL,13,Fthe "thoughtful" pre-sentence report
OL,14,Fwhich deemed his remorse to be
OL,15,Fsuperficial and not genuine.
OL,17,FJudge Daniel Williams told the
OL,18,Fdefendant he had "quickly worked" his
OL,19,Fway into the victim's life, with his
OL,20,Fmotivation "soon becoming clear" as he
OL,21,Fbegan pestering her for money.
